Definition: used to introduce a logical conclusion) from that fact or reason or as a result
Example: therefore X must be true; the eggs were fresh and hence satisfactory; we were young and thence optimistic; it is late and thus we must go; the witness is biased and so cannot be trusted
Synonyms: hence, thence, thus, so, used, to, introduce, a, logical, conclusion, from, that, fact, or, reason, as, result, X, must, be, true, the, eggs, were, fresh, and, satisfactory, we, young, optimistic, it, is, late, go, witness, biased, cannot, trusted
Category: adv.all
